The paper proposes a novel approach for feature selection using neural networks and conditional mutual information estimation. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of k-NN and feature mapping also suggests a focus on data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the application of the proposed method to datacenter hard disk drive failures indicates a potential interest in systems and networking (cs.SI).
